casebody.data:
OLD CUTLER GLEN HOMEOWNERS ASSOCIATION, INC., Appellant(s)/petitioner(s),
v.
MICHAEL WEINER, M.D., P.A. PROFIT SHARING PLAN, et al., Appellee(s)/respondent(s), CASE NO.: 3D17-1033 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. OCTOBER 30, 2017 LOGUE, LUCK and LINDSEY, JJ., concur.

ORDERED that appellee's motion to dismiss appeal is granted, and this appeal from the Circuit Court for Miami-Dade County, Florida is hereby dismissed for failure to file an initial brief.

Appellant's motion to consolidate cases, dispense with record on appeal from second case, and to modify briefing schedule is hereby denied as moot.

Appellee's motion for attorney's fees is conditionally granted subject to it prevailing in Third District Court of Appeal case number 3D17-2088.
